### Multi-Column Layout

**CSS Multi-Column** flows content into multiple columns, like a newspaper.

---

### Column Properties

| Property | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `column-count` | Number of columns |
| `column-width` | Minimum width of each column |
| `columns` | Shorthand for count and width |
| `column-gap` | Gap between columns |
| `column-rule` | Line between columns |
| `column-span` | Element spans all columns |
| `column-fill` | How columns are filled |

---

### Column Count

```css
.container {
  column-count: 3; /* Always 3 columns */
}
```

---

### Column Width

```css
.container {
  column-width: 300px; /* Columns at least 300px wide */
  /* Browser creates as many 300px columns as fit */
}
```

---

### Columns Shorthand

```css
.container {
  columns: 3;           /* column-count: 3 */
  columns: 300px;       /* column-width: 300px */
  columns: 3 300px;     /* 3 columns, each 300px */
}
```

---

### Column Gap and Rule

```css
.container {
  column-count: 3;
  column-gap: 40px;
  column-rule: 2px solid #ddd;  /* Line between columns */
}
```

---

### Column Span

```css
.title {
  column-span: all;  /* Spans across all columns */
}

.paragraph {
  column-span: none; /* Default - stays in column flow */
}
```

---

### Column Fill

```css
.container {
  column-fill: auto;     /* Columns filled sequentially */
  column-fill: balance;  /* Equal height columns (default) */
}
```

---

### When to Use Multi-Column

```css
/* Long reading content */
.article {
  columns: 300px;
  column-gap: 40px;
  column-rule: 1px solid #eee;
}

/* Card layout (better to use Grid) - prefer Grid for cards */
```

> **Best Practice:** Use multi-column for **text content** (like articles). Use CSS Grid for **component layouts** (cards, galleries).
